sentences: Betty Wishnick-Freeman (2 June 1921 – 3 January 2009) was an American philanthropist and photographer.
Freeman's second marriage was to the Italian sculptor and painter Franco Assetto (1911-1991), with whom she lived half of each year in Turin.
She had originally trained to be a concert pianist, practicing six to eight hours per day for twenty years, but eventually, by the mid-1960s, gave up this dream to pursue concert managing.
